-- Canadian Western Bank Increases CEO Pollock’s Pay to C$3 Million
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2012-01-26T22:16:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-26/canadian-western-bank-increases-ceo-pollock-s-pay-to-c-3-million.html
Canadian Western Bank (CWB) , the country’s
eighth-biggest lender, awarded Chief Executive Officer Larry Pollock C$3.04 million ($3.03 million) in compensation for 2011,
a 1 percent increase from a year earlier.  Pollock, 65, received a salary of C$680,000 and C$2.36
million in bonus, share-based awards,  stock options  and other
compensation for the year ended Oct. 31, according to a filing
today by the Edmonton, Alberta-based bank. Pollock’s pay was
C$3.01 million in 2010.  Canadian Western said Dec. 5 that annual  profit  rose 9
percent to C$178.1 million for the fiscal year on record
revenue. Canadian Western has reported 94 consecutive quarters
of profit, a record among the country’s banks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
